    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ah, I see -- this is a feature request, not a bug report.  The description was a misleading here; it made it sound like the debugger *does* determine a reason string when there is source, but not when there isn't.  When in fact, it does not determine a a reason string regardless.  It's just that, if there's source, you can often manually determine the reason string anyway by stepping through to the end.\r\n\r\nOK.  So you want us to determine (and display) the reason string in case of a revert.  Since that's a new feature rather than a bugfix I might not get to it immediately, but it does mesh nicely with some other things I was planning on doing, so I should get to this pretty soon.  Thanks for bringing this up!",
